<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 3:42PM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Pleasants, northeastern Ritchie, northwestern Doddridge and Tyler
Counties through 430 PM EDT...
At 342 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Middlebourne, moving southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Middlebourne, West Union, Arvilla, Alma, Point Lookout, Wick,
Mountain, Lima and Canton.
This includes Route 50 in West Virginia between mile markers 49 and
55.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
